==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adulteration
<hw>A*dul`ter*a"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adulteratio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of adulterating;
corruption, or debasement (esp. of food or drink) by foreign
mixture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The shameless <qex>adulteration</qex> of the coin.</q>
<rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An adulterated state or product.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adulterator</ent>⟦br⟧
